                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-277" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-277" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN NEWMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carman. Mary Blazby is my wife's sister—in</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183506150033"></xptr>
               <p>April, 1828, I witnessed her marriage to the prisoner, at Stepney church—the prisoner was a journeyman weaver—his wife was servant to Squire Skilbeck—they lived together as man and wife, and had one child, but that is dead lately—they did not live very happily together—I do not know when he left my sister-in-law—he followed the weaving a short time—I believe she left service and kept his house—she is alive and is here.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-278" type="witnessName">
