                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-278" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY POOLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I have been married to the prisoner seven years, on the 21st of last April.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-279" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-279" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-279" type="surname" value="POOLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-279" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK POOLE</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner is ray son—I heard of his first mar<lb></lb>riage, but was not present—they lived together as man and wife—I was present at his marriage on the 25th of June, at Leyton, to Emma Louisa Hawke—I cannot say what year it was in—I did not take that notice—they have been living together ever since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-280" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-280" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-280" type="surname" value="POOLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-280" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH POOLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the prisoner's mother. He has been guard to an omnibus for three years—I was present when he was married to Emma Louisa Hawke, at Leyton Church, Essex, but did not notice the year—I knew he lived with Mary Blazby—she passed by the name of Poole—they said they were married, but I did not know that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-281" type="witnessName">
